document_data.name: Mosque of Free Haku
document_data.mainbody: The '''Mosque of Free Haku''' was located in [[Huzuz]] in [[1367 DR]].{{AQ-time}}
document_data.Location: This temple could be found in the [[Pilgrims' District]] of the City of Delights.
document_data.Structure: The mosque of [[Haku]] was open to the wind on the first floor, honoring Haku's preaching of freedom. This mosque did not have a dome, allowing worshipers to sleep on the roof where they could enjoy the nightly breezes.
document_data.Inhabitants: High Priest Imam [[Gholam ibn Jubair]] was the head of the mosque. He supervised around 200 lesser-ranking priests of Haku and other laymen.
